if I was in charge of K-12 curriculum, I would spend at least a month a year working on being able to intuit different units of measure; being able to eyeball a gram of different materials, carry a pound for an hour, carry 100 pounds for 10 minutes, eyeball a foot, a meter, 100 meters, understanding the volume of a liter, the difference between carrying a 20l backpack and a 60l backpack for a day, knowing how many watts/hour your devices pull
